_An implementation that could work_

``` javascript
/**
 * Creates an object where each property is composed from
 * an element of keys (key) and the value from callback(key).
 *
 * @param  {array} keys The array of keys.
 * @param  {function} [callback=_.identity] The callback(key) that returns the object:s values.
 * @return {object} Returns an object composed of the given keys and callback(key) for values.
 */
_.objectMap = function(keys, callback) {
  callback = callback || _.identity;
  var object = {};
  for(var index = 0, len = keys.length; index < len; ++index) {
    var key = keys[index];
    object[key] = callback(key);
  }
  return object;
};
```

Would it be possible for Lodash to facilitate checking whether a given object contains all the `property:value` pair(s) of another object?

What I have in mind is an equivalent to Should.js's [`.containEql`](https://github.com/shouldjs/should.js#containeqlothervalue) and/or [`.containDeep`](https://github.com/shouldjs/should.js#containdeepothervalue) (but returning a boolean instead of throwing an assertion error).

Here's a quick rundown of the existing ways to achieve this desired behavior:

``` js
function objectContains(container, contained) {
    // Underscore:
    return _.matches(contained)(container);

    // Lodash:
    return _.isEqual(_.pick(container, _.keys(contained)), contained);

    // native ES5 (shallow comparison):
    return Object.keys(contained).every(function(key) {
        return contained[key] === container[key];
    });
}

// Usage:
objectContains({a:1, b:2, c:3}, {a:1, b:2});      // true
objectContains({a:1, b:2, c:3}, {a:1, b:3});      // false
objectContains({a:1, b:2, c:3}, {a:1, b:2, d:4}); // false
```

As you can see, the Lodash way is quite convoluted. Am I overlooking something?

Also, as far as I can see, this feature could use most of the [`_.isEqual`](https://lodash.com/docs#isEqual) logic, the only difference is that it will still return `true` when the first object has properties which are not contained in the second object.

