Hi there,
Currently there is no way (that I know of at least) to append arguments (rather than prepending them), while also setting the context.

There is currently `_.partial` and `_.partialRight`, which will set the arguments, but they don't allow for setting the context.

The use case I'm imagining, for instance is something like:

```
var obj = {
   handleEvent: function(event, optionalArg1, optionalArg2){
      if (event.type == 'click'){
         // do something
      }
      else if (event.type == 'mouseenter') {
        console.log(optionalArg1);
      }
   }
};

jQuery('#docs').on({
   click: _.bind(obj.handleEvent, obj),
   mouseenter: _.bind(obj.handleEvent, obj, 100)
});
```

I'm sure I could just nest `_.partialRight` inside of `_.bind`, but this seems odd to only support it for partial but not bind since `_.bind` is already a superset of `_.partial` (in that it supports both partial application of arguments and context setting), and it also seems like it would be creating some redundant function wrappers.

I would love to get your thoughts on this.

